  "prompt": "What is the best open-source captive portal for a WiFi Hospot?",
  "response": "There are several open-source captive portal solutions available for setting up a Wi-Fi hotspot, each with its features and strengths. Here are some of the most popular options:\n\n1. **CoovaChilli**:\n   - CoovaChilli is a widely used open-source captive portal software that allows for the management of Wi-Fi networks, especially in conjunction with a RADIUS server. \n   - It supports various authentication methods, including social media logins and guest access.\n   - It is suitable for businesses, public hotspots, and larger networks.\n\n2. **OpenWISP**:\n   - OpenWISP is a collection of various open-source components to build a captive portal, which can be integrated into various web frameworks. \n   - It supports authentication via RADIUS and can be customized to fit specific needs. It\u2019s great for developers looking to create tailored solutions.\n\n3. **pfSense with Captive Portal**:\n   - pfSense is a popular open-source firewall/router operating system that includes built-in captive portal functionality.\n   - It provides robust features for managing network traffic and is suitable for small to medium-sized enterprises. \n   - The captive portal can be configured for guest access with options for user authentication and data usage monitoring.\n\n4. **ZebraZapps**:\n   - ZebraZapps is another open-source captive portal with an easy-to-use interface and support for various authentication methods.\n   - It's ideal for small businesses looking for a straightforward solution.\n\n5. **Chillispot**:\n   - Chillispot is an older option but has been used historically in many hotspots.\n   - It is primarily used with Linux-based systems and supports several authentication methods.\n\n6. **Ntopng**:\n   - While primarily a network monitoring tool, Ntopng has features that can work well for creating captive portal experiences, especially if you are focusing on analytics and network visibility.\n\nWhen choosing the best open-source captive portal for your Wi-Fi hotspot, consider factors like ease of installation, user interface, available features, community support, and specific use cases. If you require a more straightforward setup, pfSense might be the best route; if you're tech-savvy and need extensive customization, OpenWISP or CoovaChilli could be preferable.",
